# NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier

**Enumeration**

`NSWhoseSpecifier` uses these constants to specify sub-elements within the collection of objects being tested that pass the specifier’s test.

## Declaration

```swift
enum SubelementIdentifier
```

## Overview

These constants are used by [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSWhoseSpecifier/startSubelementIdentifier], [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSWhoseSpecifier/startSubelementIdentifier], [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSWhoseSpecifier/endSubelementIdentifier], and [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSWhoseSpecifier/endSubelementIdentifier].

## Constants

- **NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier.indexSubelement**: An element at a given index that meets the specifier test.
- **NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier.everySubelement**: Every element that meets the specifier test.
- **NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier.middleSubelement**: The middle element that meets the specifier test.
- **NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier.randomSubelement**: Any element that meets the specifier test.
- **NSWhoseSpecifier.SubelementIdentifier.noSubelement**: No sub-element met the specifier test. Valid only for specifying the end sub-element.; that is, there is no end, so consider all elements.

## Initializers

- **init(rawValue:)**

## Conforms To

- BitwiseCopyable
- Equatable
- Hashable
- RawRepresentable
- Sendable
- SendableMetatype
